AB  - The paper reports the results of an econometric analysis of the industrial economic determinants of manufacturing ownership in five less developed countries - Brazil, India, Mexico, South Africa and South Korea. The analysis provides added empirical support for the industrial economic analysis of the role of multinational firms in industry; it extends the analysis to account for the roles of private local and state-owned enterprises; and it provides a basis for evaluation of the relative importance of market and political processes in the five countries.
